<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="404" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,638,1383]" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,386,638,663]" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">Material examined.</emphasis>
Adult, Jardin Magguy, N16°01.257', W61°39.283', 
<quantity box="[980,1053,639,663]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.83" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" unit="m" value="283.0">283 m</quantity>
asl, pumice-based soils of humid montane forest.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,638,1383]" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">
Adult specimen 
<date box="[382,451,710,735]" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" value="1935-10-02">
35 x 
<quantity box="[437,451,711,735]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" unit="mm" value="2.0">2</quantity>
</date>
mm, prostomium tentacular, purple pigmented only in head segments (
<figureCitation box="[1245,1312,710,735]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1810,1832]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1438,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,1438,1788]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 6. Periscolex sp., live photo." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/272509/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), no dorsal pores, spermathecal pores in CD 5/6, nephridial pores at D. Clitellum annular xiv–xxii, tubercula pubertatis xx–xxi. Setae lumbricine, widely paired, AB ventral, CD lateral, AB&lt;CD. Gizzard in vi, intestinal origin xvi, typhlosole origin xx, with vertical flanges xx–xxvi, then simple ribbon. One pair calciferous glands attached to dorsal esophageal wall in vii, trabecular sac with fluted internal wall and a central column. Holonephridia long slender folded tubules, large peptonephridial masses on anterior faces of septa in iv, v. Holandric, free; seminal vesicle of xi within that segment, vesicle originating in xii passes through 
<date box="[869,977,927,951]" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" value="2013-12-13">12/13/ 13</date>
/14 as a thin tube, expanded in xiv, xv. Spermathecae paired in vi, placed laterally below nephridiopore, basal bulbous portion with sperm, apical narrower sac; nearly sessile on body wall.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="404" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,638,1383]" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1324200693" collectorName="SW Basse Terre &amp; C. Fragoso" country="Mexico" location="Central America" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" specimenCount="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1034,1059]" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">Remarks</emphasis>
. By somatic characters other than the setae this is in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Cognetti, 1905" authorityName="Cognetti" authorityYear="1905" box="[1076,1380,1034,1059]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Periscolex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1076,1194,1035,1059]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">Periscolex</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cognetti" box="[1206,1380,1034,1059]" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" refString="Cognetti di Martiis, L. (1905) Oligocheti raccolti nel Darien dal Dr. E. Festa. Bollettino dei Musei di Zoologia ed Anatomia comparata della Reale Universita di Torino, 20 (495), 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="1905">Cognetti, 1905</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, one species of which was previously found in 
<collectorName box="[617,797,1071,1095]" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">SW Basse Terre</collectorName>
in the Monts Caraibes range and described in Csuzdi and 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,335,1106,1131]" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" refString="Csuzdi, Cs. &amp; Pavlicek, T. (2009) New records of earthworms from Guadeloupe with description of a new species (Oligochaeta: Glossoscolecidae, Acanthodrilidae, Megascolecidae and Eudrilidae). Opuscula Zoologica Hungarica, 40 (1), 9 - 15." type="journal article">Pavliček (2009)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Csuzdi &amp; Pavlicek, 2009" authorityName="Csuzdi &amp; Pavlicek" authorityYear="2009" box="[348,836,1106,1131]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Periscolex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="nevoi">
<emphasis box="[348,537,1107,1131]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">Periscolex nevoi</emphasis>
Csuzdi &amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pavlicek" box="[667,836,1106,1131]" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" refString="Csuzdi, Cs. &amp; Pavlicek, T. (2009) New records of earthworms from Guadeloupe with description of a new species (Oligochaeta: Glossoscolecidae, Acanthodrilidae, Megascolecidae and Eudrilidae). Opuscula Zoologica Hungarica, 40 (1), 9 - 15." type="journal article" year="2009">Pavliček, 2009</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is perichaetine, is greenish brown dorsally, and has three pairs of spermathecae. The species reported here is lumbricine, unpigmented except for the purple head segments, and has one pair of spermathecae in vi. Lumbricine species are 
<taxonomicName authority="Cognetti, 1905" authorityName="Cognetti" authorityYear="1905" box="[1026,1400,1178,1203]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Periscolex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="brachycystis">
<emphasis box="[1026,1040,1179,1202]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1058,1198,1179,1203]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">brachycystis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cognetti" box="[1216,1391,1178,1203]" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" refString="Cognetti di Martiis, L. (1905) Oligocheti raccolti nel Darien dal Dr. E. Festa. Bollettino dei Musei di Zoologia ed Anatomia comparata della Reale Universita di Torino, 20 (495), 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="1905">Cognetti, 1905</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Michaelsen, 1900" authorityName="Michaelsen" authorityYear="1900" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Periscolex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="colombianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">P. colombianus</emphasis>
(Michaelsen, 1900)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Zicsi, 1992" authorityName="Zicsi" authorityYear="1992" box="[540,866,1214,1239]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Periscolex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ecuadoriensis">
<emphasis box="[540,726,1214,1238]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">P. ecuadoriensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zicsi" box="[734,866,1214,1239]" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" refString="Zicsi, A. (1992) Uber weitere neue und bekannte Arten der Gattung Periscolex (Oligochaeta: Glossoscolecidae) Regenwurmer aus Sudamerika 16. Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 99, 1 - 7. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 79830" type="journal article" year="1992">Zicsi, 1992</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Zicsi &amp; Csuzdi, 1999" authorityName="Zicsi &amp; Csuzdi" authorityYear="1999" box="[929,1405,1214,1239]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Periscolex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="guayamerinensis">
<emphasis box="[929,1148,1215,1238]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">P. guayamerinensis</emphasis>
Zicsi &amp; Csuzdi, 
<quantity box="[1349,1405,1215,1239]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.07746" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" unit="in" value="1999.0">1999</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in South and 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:440C87ADFF9BC95DFF19C334FDE6FA8D:C97A6060FF9BC95DFE9EC5CFFE5AFB11" box="[272,459,1250,1275]" country="Mexico" name="Central America" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">Central America</location>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Zicsi" box="[475,600,1250,1275]" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" refString="Zicsi, A. (1992) Uber weitere neue und bekannte Arten der Gattung Periscolex (Oligochaeta: Glossoscolecidae) Regenwurmer aus Sudamerika 16. Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 99, 1 - 7. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 79830" type="journal article" year="1992">Zicsi 1992</bibRefCitation>
), plus records of 
<taxonomicName box="[796,965,1251,1275]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Periscolex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="brachycystis">
<emphasis box="[796,965,1251,1275]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">P. brachycystis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1002,1087,1250,1275]" name="Mexico" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1144,1203,1250,1275]" name="Cuba" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">Cuba</collectingCountry>
(
<collectorName box="[1220,1344,1251,1275]" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">C. Fragoso</collectorName>
<emphasis box="[1352,1412,1251,1275]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">in litt</emphasis>
.). The present individual does not belong to any of the described lumbricine 
<taxonomicName box="[1033,1151,1286,1310]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Periscolex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1033,1151,1286,1310]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">Periscolex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, having a single pair of spermathecae in vi and tubercula pubertatis limited to two segments. It is closest to 
<taxonomicName box="[1101,1269,1323,1347]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Periscolex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="13" pageNumber="404" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="brachycystis">
<emphasis box="[1101,1269,1323,1347]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="404">P. brachycystis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on size, tubercula pubertatis and clitellum location.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
